<style>
    html {
        background-color: #f5f0ff !important;
    }

    .cCenterPanel {
        padding: 0px;
        margin: 0px;
    }

    .contentRegion {
        padding: 0 !important;
    }

    .slds-form-element__label {
        color: #000 !important;
    }

    .slds-tabs_default__link {
        text-decoration: none !important;
    }

    .slds-backdrop {
        background-color: #5c3e99 !important;
    }

    .modal-spinner .slds-spinner_container{
        background-color: #f5f0ff !important;
    }
</style>

<script>
    // ----------------------------------------------------------------
    // Prevent auto-zooming on iOS when input fields receive focus.
    // ----------------------------------------------------------------

    let setViewportAttempts = 0;

    function setViewport() {
        // Only attempt to set viewport 10 times.
        // It's necessary to attempt it multiple times because the viewport <meta> element isn't in the DOM initially.
        // Presumably it's getting added dynamically by Javascript so this code needs to wait until it's there to update it.
        if (setViewportAttempts === 10) {
            return;
        }

        setViewportAttempts++;

        setTimeout(() => {
            let viewPortElement = document.querySelector('meta[name="viewport"]');
            if (viewPortElement) {
                viewPortElement.setAttribute('content', 'initial-scale=1.0, maximum-scale=1.0, minimum-scale=1.0, minimal-ui');
            } else {
                setViewport();
            }
        }, 100);
    }

    setViewport();

    // ----------------------------------------------------------------
</script>
